02.03.2014 Today, the network has got preliminary test build of Windows 8.1 Update 1 - a major update
that Microsoft is preparing to users Windows 8.1.
Update brings a number of improvements and modifications of the user interface, as well as a number of
functions for the corporate sector.
Judging by the build number is compiled January 14, 2014 at 2:00 37 minutes PST.
Major changes in the Windows 8.1 Update 1 affect the user's interaction with contemporary (Modern)
interface. So, in today's applications appeared titles and closing cross, they now can be fixed in the
taskbar on the desktop works and preview applications that are running.
On the home screen in the upper right part came off button, search, and when working with tiles with the
mouse right button is now called classical context menu.
Changes affected and Internet Explorer - it has been updated to version 11.0.3, moreover, appeared
(though not active in this assembly) Enterprise mode (EMIE), which provides compatibility with older
versions of IE to run correctly outside superstructures and intranet resources.
